<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1518,1725]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,1518,1544]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Comments:</emphasis>
A single female specimen was collected, which could not be assigned to any described species due to the difficulty of identifying this semaphoront. The fastigium of the frons is small, 
<emphasis box="[1088,1121,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">ca.</emphasis>
half of the length of vertex fastigium, with a median ocellus as long as half of the length of the scape. The fastigium of the vertex is rounded and red. A yellow line departs from the fastigium of the vertex and reaches the posterior border of pronotum. The 
<emphasis box="[151,310,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">humeral sinus</emphasis>
is protruded, and the lateral lobes of the pronotum present small reddish punctations. The costal and anal margins of the tegmina are parallel, and a black punctation appear on the beginning of A2 vein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
